This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it proposes a new architecture for representing an index that improves performance on conjunctive, phrasal, and proximity queries. It also discusses the compression of inverted indices, which is a common technique used in information retrieval systems. 

It could also belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category as it proposes a new data structure for representing an index. 

The Database (cs.DB) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses techniques for storing and retrieving data efficiently. 

The Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category is a less likely possibility as the paper does not explicitly discuss machine learning techniques, but it does propose a new architecture that could potentially be used in machine learning applications. 

The Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category is also a less likely possibility as the paper does not explicitly discuss cryptography or security, but the techniques discussed could potentially be used in secure information retrieval systems.
